data.title: 1150 Fifth Avenue
data.text: Designed by famous architect J. E. R Carpenter in 1924, and directly overlooking Central Park, this prestigious Upper East Side prewar building is in the finest Carnegie Hill location on New Yorkâ€™s famous Fifth Avenue. Many of the apartments feature Central Park views and most have wood burning fireplaces. Carnegie Hill is known for exclusive private schools, excellent public schools, Museum Mile, The Guggenheim Museum, Central Park and the Conservatory Garden. A fully equipped playground is directly across the street from the building. The area features elegant shopping and dining on Madison Avenue.
